git diff -- cached
command is used to show the differences between the files in your staging area (index) and your last commit.

git show
command is used to view the changes made in the most recent commit.

clt z
to stop git diff or git show

git reset --soft HEAD~1
command is used to undo last unpushed commit

git add -p <file_name?
command is used to patch changes to be added to staging

git commit -v
command allows user to and commment and commit staged changes in command line. you can also view you changes inline

